cted that xxx@domain.extension is not accepted (for now only email like xxx.yyy@domain.extension)\r\n","created_on":"2014-12-12T16:25:11Z","details":[]},{"id":4570,"user":{"id":761,"name":"Battaglia Marc"},"created_on":"2014-12-15T07:58:08Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"fixed_version_id","old_value":"161","new_value":"162"}]},{"id":4587,"user":{"id":16,"name":"Portier Thomas"},"notes":"Ok for ftp, the pattern will be : \r\n((http://|https://|ftp://)(www.)?(([a-zA-Z0-9-]){2,}.){1,4}([a-zA-Z]){2,6}(/([a-zA-Z-_/.0-9#:?=&;,]*)?)?)\r\n\r\nBut I don't think that stereotype \"link\" should be used for email? In my case I use the stereotype text for email.\r\nThere should be an other stereotype specific for the mail or the ability to add a pattern as an option.","created_on":"2014-12-16T10:52:53Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"assigned_to_id","old_value":"16","new_value":"3"}]},{"id":4589,"user":{"id":761,"name":"Battaglia Marc"},"notes":"","created_on":"2014-12-18T09:21:57Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"fixed_version_id","old_value":"162","new_value":"163"}]},{"id":4602,"user":{"id":3,"name":"Magoni Bruno"},"notes":"","created_on":"2014-12-19T09:16:43Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"tracker_id","old_value":"1","new_value":"3"},{"property":"attr","name":"status_id","old_value":"2","new_value":"6"}]},{"id":4603,"user":{"id":3,"name":"Magoni Bruno"},"notes":"","created_on":"2014-12-19T09:17:04Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"status_id","old_value":"6","new_value":"1"}]},{"id":4604,"user":{"id":3,"name":"Magoni Bruno"},"notes":"Need further discussion about what covers exactly such stereotype...","created_on":"2014-12-19T09:17:52Z","details":[{"property":"attr","name":"status_id","old_value":"1","new_value":"7"},{"property":"attr","name":"assigned_to_id","old_value":"3","new_value":"282"},{"property":"attr","name":"fixed_version_id","old_value":"163","new_value":"114"}]},{"id":4618,"user":{"id":3,"name":"Magoni Bruno"},"notes":"Sorry S